42:00.518 --> 42:01.985
No, that's it.

42:03.621 --> 42:07.648
Yeah, yeah, I said, you know, you're
really messing with my mind, man.

42:08.058 --> 42:09.650
Yeah, okay.

42:10.094 --> 42:12.255
Yeah. I'll see you later.

42:17.301 --> 42:19.326
What kind of car are we talking about?

42:20.304 --> 42:21.862
Well, it's an Accord.

42:22.039 --> 42:24.769
1988. It's right over there.

42:25.543 --> 42:26.601
Well....

42:27.344 --> 42:28.868
Easy enough to replace the Serpentine belt.

42:29.046 --> 42:30.638
I don't know why the ignition won't fire, though.

42:30.781 --> 42:32.806
Who knows. Could be the timing belt.

42:34.184 --> 42:36.277
How much is a new Serpentine belt?

42:38.689 --> 42:39.883
A hundred bucks.

42:40.224 --> 42:44.320
125. Depends if we have to order a
new one. I'll have to check stock.

42:45.663 --> 42:48.063
And it'll be 50 for labor.

42:49.700 --> 42:51.895
That's the best you'll find. I promise that.

42:52.036 --> 42:55.563
Okay. And what about a timing
belt? How much is that?

42:55.839 --> 42:59.775
Could be a little bit more, but I
won't know until I have a look.

43:00.377 --> 43:01.935
Okay.

43:02.146 --> 43:06.742
And we're going to have to tow it
over, I guess. That adds another 50.

43:09.253 --> 43:10.948
But it's just right there.

43:11.288 --> 43:15.315
Well, it's always 50. But there's
no mileage here. So it's just 50.

43:21.699 --> 43:24.099
30 bucks. I'll give you a deal. .

43:26.670 --> 43:27.659
Yeah.

45:13.210 --> 45:14.472
How's the dog?

45:18.282 --> 45:19.840
No news.

45:20.484 --> 45:22.213
No luck at the pound?

45:23.921 --> 45:25.388
Not yet.

45:29.226 --> 45:32.491
I had a Collie once that was gone for
two weeks before he came home.

45:33.097 --> 45:36.294
They'll find her. They always get their dog.

45:37.301 --> 45:39.963
Yeah, I sure hope so.

45:41.405 --> 45:46.240
Could I trade you for a quarter? I need
to use that pay phone over there.

45:46.343 --> 45:49.540
All I've got is change and it only takes quarters.

45:49.980 --> 45:51.538
Lots of minutes. Feel free.

45:51.849 --> 45:52.838
No, no.

45:52.983 --> 45:55.247
No one uses a pay phone anymore. Come on.

46:00.557 --> 46:01.990
Thanks.

46:18.976 --> 46:23.811
Hi, my name is Wendy Carroll.
I lost my dog Lucy and I....

46:26.116 --> 46:27.981
Yeah, yeah, hi.

46:28.986 --> 46:32.444
I was just calling to check and see
if there was any new information.

46:37.594 --> 46:42.361
Okay, all right, I understand. I'll keep
checking. Okay. Thank you. Bye.

47:02.920 --> 47:04.353
How late are you here tonight?

47:04.488 --> 47:06.479
Eight o'clock. Eight to eight.

47:06.623 --> 47:07.487
Okay.

47:08.458 --> 47:10.824
Better than my last job. I'll tell you that.

47:11.528 --> 47:14.053
That was all night, every night.

47:16.533 --> 47:18.831
Not a lot of jobs around here, huh?.

47:19.336 --> 47:20.530
I'll say.

47:21.104 --> 47:23.038
I don't know what the people do all day.

47:24.174 --> 47:27.610
Use to be a mill. But that's
been closed a long time now.

47:28.445 --> 47:29.605
Don't know what they do.

47:35.052 --> 47:37.885
You can't get a job without an address anyway...

47:38.388 --> 47:40.049
...or a phone.

47:40.290 --> 47:44.420
You can't get an address without an
address. You can't get a job without a job.

47:44.928 --> 47:46.327
It's all fixed.

47:46.496 --> 47:48.657
That's why I'm going to Alaska.

47:51.368 --> 47:53.199
I hear they need people.

47:54.338 --> 47:56.101
I hear it's really pretty up there.

47:56.240 --> 47:57.332
Yeah.

48:00.210 --> 48:02.542
You know, if you need a contact
for the pound or anything...

48:02.679 --> 48:05.239
...I'm just standing here with my
hands in my pockets all day.

48:08.118 --> 48:10.586
You can use my phone
number if you like, you know.

48:12.956 --> 48:14.218
Yeah.

48:17.527 --> 48:19.995
I might do that. That'd be good.

48:42.719 --> 48:46.917
floppy ears, sharp eyes,
yellowish-brown, friendly face

49:09.579 --> 49:11.308
I'm LOST!!!

49:17.487 --> 49:20.012
You lost your dog?

49:20.457 --> 49:22.322
Wow, bummer.

49:22.626 --> 49:24.457
Wow, where did you lose it?

49:25.062 --> 49:27.587
You don't know? Well, I guess if you
knew, you'd know where to find it.

49:27.731 --> 49:29.028
Yeah, I guess so.

49:29.132 --> 49:32.192
Well, that's too bad. If I see it,
I'll give you a call. Good luck.

49:32.336 --> 49:34.065
Thanks. Appreciate that.

50:27.758 --> 50:29.089
Lucy!

50:43.673 --> 50:44.765
Anything?

50:45.308 --> 50:46.639
Afraid not.

50:48.111 --> 50:51.137
They came and rolled your
car away about an hour ago.

50:54.384 --> 50:58.218
You know, I was remembering today,
when I was a boy I'd go hunting...

50:58.655 --> 51:00.555
...and sometimes we'd lose the hound...

51:00.690 --> 51:03.488
...so my daddy would take his
coat and leave it in the woods...

51:03.627 --> 51:06.391
...the last place that he saw the dog.

51:06.563 --> 51:10.226
And after supper he'd come
back to fetch the coat...

51:11.668 --> 51:14.660
...and more often than not he'd
come back with the dog as well.

51:16.773 --> 51:18.502
Could I use that phone again?

51:18.642 --> 51:19.836
Sure.

51:21.778 --> 51:23.268
Thank you.

51:32.656 --> 51:36.820
Hello, I'm calling to check on a dog
that I reported missing. Lucy.

51:39.463 --> 51:42.899
Yeah, sorry, I've just been away from my
phone and so I thought I would check.

51:43.900 --> 51:45.527
Okay.

51:45.869 --> 51:47.461
Okay. Thank you. Bye-bye.

51:55.846 --> 51:57.438
Wait.

51:58.815 --> 52:01.716
Did you say that the dog would,
the dog came back to a coat?

52:02.252 --> 52:03.446
Yes, indeed.

52:03.620 --> 52:06.111
That's how I remember it.

52:41.191 --> 52:42.590
Lucy!

52:45.795 --> 52:46.921
Lu!

53:12.222 --> 53:13.314
Lu?

54:25.328 --> 54:27.296
Please, please, please.

55:46.343 --> 55:47.674
Man.

56:31.020 --> 56:32.715
Don't look at me.

56:39.963 --> 56:41.828
This is a steep hill, huh?

56:43.133 --> 56:44.657
Ain't it?

56:45.502 --> 56:49.438
Those kids coming down on a cardboard...

56:50.006 --> 56:51.667
...they're having some fun.

56:54.878 --> 56:59.508
Of course if that cardboard wasn't so worn
and old, you know, they'd slide better, right?

57:16.633 --> 57:19.033
I don't like this place.

57:22.672 --> 57:24.606
You know, it's the fucking people.

57:25.175 --> 57:27.200
The fucking people that bother me.

57:28.778 --> 57:30.177
God, they have attitude.

57:34.884 --> 57:35.942
I mean...

57:40.457 --> 57:42.049
...I'm out here...

57:43.526 --> 57:45.551
...just trying to be a good boy...

57:46.930 --> 57:49.922
...and it's just like they don't want to let me...

57:51.468 --> 57:52.730
...you know?

57:54.037 --> 57:58.974
I mean, they treat me like
trash, like I ain't got no rights.

58:03.213 --> 58:04.680
I mean...

58:05.748 --> 58:08.911
...they can smell the weakness on you.

58:10.787 --> 58:13.847
Move it along, move it along. Fuck you.

58:14.123 --> 58:16.182
You know? Fuck you!

58:18.094 --> 58:23.031
I mean, they gotta know I've killed
over 700 people with my bare hands.

58:33.643 --> 58:35.270
We lost, man.

58:39.048 --> 58:41.141
Fuck if I know.

01:00:28.658 --> 01:00:30.683
Hang on, girl.

01:00:31.294 --> 01:00:32.727
I'm coming.

01:01:59.348 --> 01:02:01.179
You look a little stricken.

01:02:01.317 --> 01:02:03.911
I've been here since eight. Where have you been?

01:02:04.053 --> 01:02:07.181
I had to take Holly's son to school.

01:02:07.323 --> 01:02:09.223
It's my day off today too.

01:02:09.926 --> 01:02:13.020
You got a call after you left
here last night. The pound.

01:02:13.296 --> 01:02:14.285
Really?

01:02:15.231 --> 01:02:16.220
Yes, indeed.

01:02:29.045 --> 01:02:31.070
Hi, this is Wendy Carroll calling.

01:02:31.247 --> 01:02:34.239
I got a message from you all
last night about my dog Lucy.

01:02:40.757 --> 01:02:42.122
Are you positive?

01:02:49.398 --> 01:02:52.526
Okay, where is she exactly?

01:02:55.104 --> 01:02:57.265
Where the 30 meets Leaf--

01:02:58.541 --> 01:03:00.975
Where the 30 meets Leaf Erickson.

01:03:05.848 --> 01:03:09.284
Okay, well, I'll be there right
away. Thank you very much.

01:03:09.552 --> 01:03:10.985
Yep. Bye-bye.

01:03:12.989 --> 01:03:14.513
All right? Good news?

01:03:14.824 --> 01:03:18.055
Yeah. That's good news, that's good news.

01:03:18.161 --> 01:03:19.423
Great.

01:03:19.562 --> 01:03:21.359
Someone took her home.

01:03:22.165 --> 01:03:25.896
Someone took her home the day she came in and
that's why they had such a hard time finding her.

01:03:26.068 --> 01:03:27.296
She's in a foster home.

01:03:27.436 --> 01:03:32.271
Great. I told you they would find
her. Let that go on the record.

01:03:32.408 --> 01:03:34.069
It's on the record.

01:03:35.278 --> 01:03:38.145
So, that's it, huh? You're gonna be pulling out?

01:03:38.314 --> 01:03:39.474
Uh-huh, that's the plan.

01:03:39.816 --> 01:03:42.148
Well, I hope it all works out.

01:03:42.318 --> 01:03:43.580
I know it will.

01:03:48.457 --> 01:03:51.153
I want you to take this. Don't argue.

01:03:51.928 --> 01:03:53.156
Just don't argue.

01:03:53.329 --> 01:03:55.024
Don't let Holly see. Just....

01:03:57.433 --> 01:04:01.893
If you ever come by here again,
you just stop by and say hi, huh?

01:04:02.905 --> 01:04:05.430
Thank you. I will.

01:04:08.044 --> 01:04:09.033
Okay.

01:04:09.178 --> 01:04:10.406
Bye-bye.

01:04:29.131 --> 01:04:30.928
Ferry Running Times

01:05:00.663 --> 01:05:01.960
Finally.

01:05:16.178 --> 01:05:17.975
-Good morning. -Morning.

01:05:19.215 --> 01:05:20.512
You're up early.

01:05:23.119 --> 01:05:25.679
You want some coffee? I think the first pot's ready.

01:05:30.126 --> 01:05:34.563
Yeah, Indiana plates. You're a
long way from home, aren't you?

01:05:36.699 --> 01:05:39.566
Got a long way to go, too.

01:05:41.304 --> 01:05:43.704
Well, the guy was right about the serpentine belt.

01:05:44.006 --> 01:05:48.033
It's cracked all over the place. Just a matter
of time before the car gave out on you.

01:05:48.210 --> 01:05:50.007
Yeah, that's what he said.

01:05:50.146 --> 01:05:52.706
He wasn't all wrong, but he wasn't all right either.

01:05:53.215 --> 01:05:56.582
The serpentine belt is worn out, but
that's not why the car won't start.

01:05:56.719 --> 01:05:57.686
No?

01:05:58.154 --> 01:05:59.951
You've got milky oil.

01:06:03.025 --> 01:06:05.118
I didn't ask you to check the oil.

01:06:05.728 --> 01:06:09.721
I'm just telling you. Look,
you snapped a piston rod.

01:06:10.032 --> 01:06:11.693
Actually, you blew the head gasket first...

01:06:12.001 --> 01:06:14.697
...water got into the cylinder
probably when you cooled it down.

01:06:15.004 --> 01:06:17.564
The rod can't compress the fluid then.

01:06:17.707 --> 01:06:21.143
And there you go, you ended up
with what the call "Hydro lock".

01:06:22.611 --> 01:06:27.310
And if you want the car to drive again,
you'd have to rebuild the whole engine.

01:06:27.583 --> 01:06:32.282
Honestly, I don't think it's what you want to do. It
would end up costing more than the car is worth.

01:06:36.659 --> 01:06:38.354
Yeah?

01:06:38.661 --> 01:06:41.095
No, I couldn't get around to it yesterday.

01:06:41.464 --> 01:06:43.455
Can you call me back later?

01:06:44.367 --> 01:06:46.358
Righto. Bye.

01:06:48.504 --> 01:06:49.994
Are you sure?

01:06:50.639 --> 01:06:52.630
Yeah. No question.

01:07:00.216 --> 01:07:01.683
How much?

01:07:02.184 --> 01:07:03.481
To fix it?

01:07:05.354 --> 01:07:06.651
Two thousand.

01:07:08.224 --> 01:07:09.782
At least two thousand.

01:07:10.226 --> 01:07:13.662
Like I said, more than the car's worth. On
the other hand, it's less than a new car.

01:07:22.304 --> 01:07:27.241
Look, I know this is bad news. It's
not what anyone ever wants to hear.

01:07:27.543 --> 01:07:31.809
But see, the thing is, the car's taking up space
out there and I need to know what to do with it.

01:07:34.216 --> 01:07:37.413
I'll tell you what, just make it 30
bucks for the tow, for the...

01:07:37.620 --> 01:07:41.386
... to junk it, and we'll take care
of everything and that'll be it.

01:07:41.557 --> 01:07:44.253
It's just that I can't just leave the
car sitting out there, it's gotta go.

01:08:12.755 --> 01:08:14.723
Okay. This is good here.

01:08:30.171 --> 01:08:31.161
Thank you.

01:10:24.687 --> 01:10:25.847
Hey, Lu.

01:10:28.757 --> 01:10:31.021
Hey, Lu! Did you miss me? Huh?

01:10:31.527 --> 01:10:33.256
You miss me? Huh?

01:10:34.430 --> 01:10:38.924
You miss me? Huh? Come here,
Luce. Come here. Did you miss me?

01:10:39.268 --> 01:10:40.496
I'm sorry. Come here.

01:10:49.044 --> 01:10:50.534
I know, I know.

01:10:52.681 --> 01:10:54.546
Come on, Lu, don't be mad.

01:10:58.887 --> 01:10:59.876
Here.

01:11:01.590 --> 01:11:03.285
I got you something.

01:11:05.427 --> 01:11:06.894
Look at that.

01:11:08.897 --> 01:11:10.330
Go get it.

01:11:10.766 --> 01:11:12.324
Good girl!

01:11:12.868 --> 01:11:15.735
You're such a good catcher, huh? Drop it.

01:11:15.871 --> 01:11:17.862
Yes, such a good dog.

01:11:18.340 --> 01:11:21.309
Go get it, Lu. Go get that stick.

01:11:21.610 --> 01:11:23.475
Good dog.

01:11:23.612 --> 01:11:25.341
You are the best catcher.

01:11:28.350 --> 01:11:29.612
Drop it, Lu.

01:11:30.853 --> 01:11:33.481
Lu. Lu, give me that stick.

01:11:33.622 --> 01:11:36.489
Give me that stick, Lu. Give me that stick.

01:11:36.625 --> 01:11:38.991
Drop it. Good dog!

01:11:39.895 --> 01:11:41.362
Good girl.

01:11:43.932 --> 01:11:45.900
It's so nice here, Lu.

01:11:58.514 --> 01:12:00.379
That man seems nice.

01:12:09.491 --> 01:12:11.925
Yeah, you got a nice yard.

01:12:20.769 --> 01:12:22.031
I'm sorry, Lu.

01:12:31.980 --> 01:12:33.777
I lost the car.

01:12:50.833 --> 01:12:52.095
You be good.

01:12:56.605 --> 01:12:57.970
I'll come back.

01:12:58.941 --> 01:13:01.569
I'm gonna make some money and I'll come back.

01:13:09.685 --> 01:13:10.982
Okay, Lu?

01:13:12.154 --> 01:13:13.416
Be good.

